primary tumor, numerous immunohistochemical stains were performed on the tissue blocks to help define a primary site. the neoplastic cells are cytokeratin cocktail (ventana ae1/ae3) and cytokeratin 8/18 (cell marque 822.1/823.1) negative and myeloperoxidase (ventana polyclonal) negative. some cd138 staining is noted but the majority of the neoplastic cells are cd138 (cell marque b-a38) negative. kappa light chains (ventana polycional) and lambda light chains (ventana polyclonal) demonstrate an approximately equal amount of staining, with heavy background staining noted. scattered cells are cd3 (cell marque polyclonal) and cd43 (ventana l60) positive but the majority of the neoplastic cells are negative with both of these markers. a cd20 (ventana l26) stain is predominantly negative. a leukocyte common antigen . stain exhibits staining similar to the cd3 and cd43 stains, with the majority of the neoplastic cells being negative with this stain. $100 (ventana polyclonal), hmb-45 (ventana hmb45), and mart-1 (ventana a103) stains are all diffusely positive in the neoplastic cells. the control stains are satisfactory. the immunohistochemical profile of this neoplasm is important dates.keyword: collected by tm589075s blood _ 10/11/22 0900 jak2 v617f mutation analysis resulted: 10/20/22 1701, result status: final result order status: completed filed by: edi, quest lab results in 10/20/22 1716 collected by: 10/11/22 0900 resulting lab: quest components component value reference range flag lab clinical indication see note _ _ quest camment c79.9 specimen source blood _ _ quest block/sample number not given _ _ quest jak2 gene, v617f, qual not detected not detected _ quest gomment interpretation see note _ _ quest comment a jak2 v617f mutation is not detected. haiying meng, m.d. #ph.d., facmg technical director, cytogenetics and genomics assay details see below — _ quest comment: this pcr-based advanced sequencing assay interrogates dna from leukocytes for the presence of mutations in codon 617 of jak2. the sensitivity of mutation detection is 5%. alterations outside of the tested areas of this gene will not be detected. synonymous or known non-synonymous polymorphic changes (snps) are not reported. jak2 v617f mutation is associated with myeloproliferative neoplasms (mpns), including polycythemia vera (pv), essential thrombocythemia (et) and primary myelofibrosis (pmf), and a small subset of other myeloid neoplasms. increasing allele burden of jak2 v617f in mpns has been shown in a number of studies to be associated with increased symptoms including pruritis, splenomegaly, and leukocytosis. results of this assay should be correlated with morphology and other laboratory testing for final diagnosis and classification. if this test is negative, additional testing that may be useful for workup of mpns, depending on presenting hematologic features , includes bcr-abl1 rearrangement (test code 91065 or 12070x) or mutational analysis of calr (et/pmf, 92475), jak2 exon 12 (pv, 92474), mpl (et/pmf, 92476) or csf3r (chronic neutrophilic leukemia, 92477). residual material from this sample may be used except for bcr-abl1 testing; call lab to add. dna was aligned to grch37(hg19) for analysis and transcript id enst00000381652 was used as reference for jak2 sequence. for additional information, please refer to http://education. questdiagnostics.com/faq/faq211 (this link is being provided for informational/educational purposes only.) printed on 2/1/23 1:41 pm page 23

important dates.keyword: received 4 cycles and treatment was discontinued due to side effects which were thought to be related to immunotherapy. patient experience uncontrolled nausea and vomiting for 10 hours which led to an inpatient admission, aki and treatment of uti. he was also on a 6-week course of steroids. we discussed extensively the risks and benefits of immunotherapy including pneumonitis, colitis, thyroiditis, permanent organ damage and even death. if he did have side effects to previous nivolumab he is at high risk of recurrence however given his young age, consequences of untreated metastatic melanoma he is agreeable to proceed with immunotherapy. we will plan on single agent pembrolizumab as his options are also limited given he is braf negative, foundation ngs ordered to be done on tissue along with liquid guardant to identify any actionable mutations. will also plan on referring patient to ohsu for consideration of clinical trials at a later date. order genetic testing due to personal and family history of cancer at a young age. patient is amenable to this will place order for invitae genetic testing. port placement scheduled 6/13/22. mri brain no evidence of intracranial metastatic disease pet ct revealed multiple foci of intense uptake throughout the peritoneum. soft tissue density in the upper midline abdomen at the lesser sac measures up to 5.4cm with maximum suv of 15. left mid abdominal bulky peritoneal soft tissue mass with maximum suv of 16. right lower quadrant soft tissue with maximum suv of 14. chaney, kenneth (mrn 27052014) printed by jennifer novotny, ma [15988] at 8/22/... page 10 of 12 o8/22/2022 mon 10:26 fax 013/018 chaney, kenneth "ken" (mrn 27052014) dob;

obtained from the submitted sample is enriched for targeted regions using a hybridization-based protocol, and sequenced using llumina technology. unless otherwise indicated, all targeted regions are sequenced with 50x depth or are supplemented with additional analysis. reads are aligned to a reference sequence (grch37), and sequence changes are identified and interpreted in the context of a single clinically relevant transcript, indicated below. enrichment and analysis focus on the coding sequence of the indicated transcripts, 20bp of flanking intronic sequence, and other specific genomic regions demonstrated to be causative of disease at the time of assay design. promoters, untranslated regions, and other non-coding regions are not otherwise interrogated. for some genes only targeted loci are analyzed {indicated in the table above). exonic deletions and duplications are called using an in-house algorithm that determines copy number at each target by comparing the read depth for each target in the proband sequence with both mean read-depth and read-depth distribution, obtained from a set of clinical samples. markers across the x and y chromosomes are analyzed for quality control purposes and may detect deviations from the expected sex chromosome complement. such deviations may be included in the report in accordance with internal guidelines. confirmation of the presence and location of reportable variants is performed based on stringent criteria established by invitae (1400 16th street, san francisco, ca 94103, #05d2040778), as needed, using one of dob: may-02-1961 | test number 1 method and limitations guardanta60 sequences 83 cancer-associated genes to identify somatic alterations. cell-free dna (cfdna) is extracted from plasma, enriched for targeted regions, and sequenced using the hlumina platform and hg19 as the reference genome. all exons are sequenced in some genes; only clinically significant exons are sequenced in other genes. the types of genomic alterations detected by guardanta60 include single nucleotide variants (snvs), gene amplifications, fusions, short insertions/deletions (indels, longest detected, 70 base pairs), and splice site disrupting events (see table 1). microsatellite instablllty (msi) is assessed for all cancer types by evaluating somatic changes in the length of repetitive sequences on the guardant360 panel. a "not detected" result in samples where the highest % cfdna is < 0.2% is an inconclusive result because it does not preclude msi-high status in tissue. tumor mutational burden (tmb) score is calculated for all cancer types from somatic snvs and indels in exons of ~ 500 genes detected in cfdna, followed by adjusting for tumor shedding levels and the size of the panel. a "not evaluable” result is an inconclusive result in samples where the evidence of tumor shedding is insufficient and it does not preclude tmb-high status in tissue, certain sample or variant characteristics, such as low cfdna concentration, may result in reduced analytic sensitivity. guardant360 cannot discern the source of circulating cfdna, and for some variants in the range of ~40 to 60% cfdna, the test cannot of amplification. as the absolute number of copies in circulation is dependent on both tumor fraction and the magnitude of the tumor amplification, amplifications are reported on a semi-quantitative scale. for ccnet, egfr, esr1 and fgfa1, three levels are reported: low {+): amplification magnitude is below the soth percentile of amplifications detected by guardant360, medium (++): amplification the circulating cell-free dna isolated from this patient's blood specimen. these genomic alterations are cancer-associated somatic variants, some of which have been assoclated with elther increased or reduced clinical response to specific treatments. the percentage of altered cell-free dna circulating (% cfdna) in blood is related to the unique tumor biology of each patient. factors that may affect a given gene in ail circulating cell-free dna present in the patient's blood sample including material derived from the tumor and healthy tissue alike. as such, the absolute level of amplification present in the blood depends both on the tumor-derived cfdna content and on the degree of amplification within that fraction and cannot be inferred from butk cfona interrogation. for example, a positive guardant360 test could represent a small population of cells with extremely high levels of the detected gene amplification. alternatively, it could represent a large population of cells with instability (msi) is assessed for all cancer types by evaluating somatic changes in the length of repetitive sequences on the guardant360 panel. a "not detected" result in samples where the highest % cfdna is < 0.2% is an inconclusive result because it does not preclude msi-high status in tissue. tumor mutational burden (tms) score is calculated for ail cancer types from somatic snvs and indels in exons of ~ 500 genes detected in cfdna, followed by adjusting for tumor shedding levels and the size of the panel. a "not evaluabie" resutt is an inconclusive result in samples where the evidence of important dates.keyword: received gammaknife to 3 lesions in brain 6/27/22. 7/6/22 started opdivo/yervoy. after 3 cycles , pet/ct finally approved to assess disease. 8/31/22 pet/ct showed 1. overall, unfavorable progression of multifocal areas of hypermetabolic soft tissue masses seen throughout the chest, abdomen, pelvis and lower extremities consistent with metastatic disease. there are increasing size of multiple nodules including intensity as well as some scattered new nodules as detailed above. 2. again seen is hypermetabolic nodules seen within both lungs consistent with metastatic disease. 3. redemonstrated is a lytic lesion of the right sacrum or soft tissue nodule within the right aspect of the spinal canal at the level of s1 consistent with metastatic disease as well. 4. additionally, apparent is a pericardial mass which extends into the left ventricular wall with a maximal suv of 23.7 compatible with metastatic disease. patient presenting for follow up. patient on yervoy+opdivo. patient seen by dr. chandra nmh melanoma team. recommendations to finish c4 of opdivo/yervoy and consider repeat imaging in 6 weeks to assess and rule out pseudoprogression. also, considering clinical trials options and possibility of ntrk inhibitor. unfortunately, transport will be primary concern for clinical trials placement. nmh lurie cancer center and nm mchenry cancer center gps/social services teams will try to assess ability to provide transport for trials placement. patient also recommended to consider palliative rt to left thigh and abdominal lesions to reduce irritation and pain. patient also having fatigue with |o therapy. acth/cortiso! levels drawn. printed on 9/22/22 3:24 pm page n northwestern nm oncology hoffman, lori a medicine 10350 haligus rd mrn: 111012043153, dob: 10/3/1967, sex: f = huntley il 60142-9585 visit date: 9/9/2022 # 3)
